<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Compound1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Compound,</orth> subst. 1) composition, mixture: <cit><quote>the poisonous simple sometimes is compacted in a pure c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 531" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 531</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with eager --s we our palates urge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 118.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 118, 2</bibl></cit>. cf. <cit><quote>to new-found methods and to --s strange,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.76.4" default="NO" valid="yes">76, 4</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 8</bibl><lb />2) mass, lump: <cit><quote>behold that c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.136" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 136</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou whoreson mad c. of majesty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.319" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 319</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>